When using the Authorization Code Flow with OAuth 2.0, it's essential to implement Proof Key for Code Exchange (PKCE) for enhanced security. PKCE generates a secret key, called the challenge code, to verify the authorization request. To implement PKCE, you'll need to add the 'code_challenge' and 'code_challenge_method' parameters to your authorization request. For example, in a TypeScript client, you can use the 'axios' library to send an authorization request with PKCE:

const axios = require('axios');
const params = {
  client_id: 'your_client_id',
  redirect_uri: 'your_redirect_uri',
  response_type: 'code',
  code_challenge: 'your_challenge_code',
  code_challenge_method: 'S256'
};
const authUrl = `https://your-oauth-server.com/oauth2/authorize?${new URLSearchParams(params).toString()}`;
axios.get(authUrl).then((response) => {
  console.log(response.data);
});

